Items.description: Washington's Colt Brennan threw two touchdown passes in the second half, and Matterral Richardson returned an interception 38 yards for a touchdown to rally the Redskins for a 30-16 victory in Sunday's Hall of Fame Game.
Items.notes: Hall of Fame Game, HALL OF FAME GAME

Items.description: Eli Manning and the Super Bowl champion New York Giants finally stumbled on the road. Only this time, it didn't really matter. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: Detroit Lions vs. New York Giants

Items.description: Brett Favre's big-play ability rubbed off on the Jets, who scored three long touchdowns in a 24-20 win over the Browns as their new star quarterback watched from the sideline. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: Cleveland Browns vs. New York Jets

Items.description: With Tom Brady having the night off, the Patriots were far from perfect in their first game after a nearly perfect season. For John Harbaugh, the Ravens' 16-15 preseason win was a good start to his head coaching career. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: New England Patriots vs. Baltimore Ravens

Items.description: Drew Brees and Matt Leinart started the preseason with near-perfection. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: Arizona Cardinals vs. New Orleans Saints

Items.description: Larry Johnson showed glimpses of his old self and Brodie Croyle hinted at what might be. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: Chicago Bears vs. Kansas City Chiefs

Items.description: A sore groin didn't slow Ben Roethlisberger and the Pittsburgh Steelers' first-string offense. Good thing, too, because the Steelers now face uncertainty at the backup quarterback position. NFL Preseason

Matt Hasselbeck was 7-of-8 for 70 yards and a touchdown and the Seahawks racked up 187 total yards in three series against the Vikings' defensive starters in a 34-17 preseason victory on Friday night. NFL Preseason

Michael Bush scored on a 5-yard touchdown run in his first game since breaking his leg in college more than 23 months ago, leading the Oakland Raiders to an 18-6 exhibition victory over the San Francisco 49ers on Friday night. NFL Preseason
Jason Campbell and Todd Collins combined to go 15-for-21 in the first half of Saturday night's 17-14 victory over the Buffalo Bills. NFL Preseason

Julius Peppers' return to form in Carolina's preseason opener didn't allow Jake Delhomme much of a chance to test his surgically repaired right elbow in the Panthers' 23-20 overtime win over Indianapolis on Saturday night. NFL Preseason
Jacksonville rested Fred Taylor and lost three fumbles but still had enough offense to beat the Falcons 20-17 on Saturday night in the preseason opener for both teams. NFL Preseason
Chad Pennington flipped through play charts on the sideline in his new Miami Dolphins jersey, watching his fellow quarterbacks audition for their jobs. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: Miami Dolphins vs. Tampa Bay Buccaneers

Items.description: David Anderson is far down Houston's depth chart at receiver, but he made the most of his opportunity in the Texans' preseason opener on Saturday night. NFL Preseason

Vince Young and LenDale White both have healthy legs, and rookie Chris Johnson gave a glimpse of why Tennessee drafted him in the first round. The Titans' passing game remains a work in progress. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: Tennessee Titans vs. St. Louis Rams

Items.description: The San Diego Chargers have few open roster spots after reaching the AFC championship game last season. But rookie Jacob Hester is making a strong case for one. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: San Diego Chargers vs. Dallas Cowboys

Items.description: Aaron Rodgers shook off a shaky start to look solid in his gig as Packers starter. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: Green Bay Packers vs. Cincinnati Bengals

Items.description: O, Canada, did Trent Edwards ever find his groove during the Buffalo Bills' debut in their new northern home away from home. NFL Preseason
Jake Delhomme fired a pass over the middle for a touchdown that was overturned. The result didn't matter so much. Delhomme's surgically repaired right elbow passed the test. NFL Preseason

Brett Favre was solid in his brief Jets debut after a week of cramming to learn his new playbook, throwing a 4-yard touchdown pass to Dustin Keller to cap his second series in a 13-10 loss to the Washington Redskins on Saturday night. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: New York Jets vs. Washington Redskins

Items.description: With no apparent timetable on Peyton Manning's return from knee surgery, the Colts were relieved that Jim Sorgi avoided critical mistakes in their 16-9 preseason victory over the Falcons on Saturday night. NFL Preseason

Tarvaris Jackson left with a knee injury in the first quarter of Saturday night's preseason game against the Baltimore Ravens, ruining an otherwise productive night for the Vikings quarterback in Minnesota's 23-15 victory. NFL Preseason
Chad Pennington is already giving the Miami Dolphins something they're not used to. NFL Preseason

Rookie running back Tim Hightower had a short touchdown run and Matt Leinart shook off a bad start and threw a 14-yard touchdown pass to Steve Breaston, leading the Arizona Cardinals to a 27-17 victory over a punchless Kansas City on Saturday night. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: Kansas City Chiefs vs. Arizona Cardinals

Items.description: Deuce McAllister made a promising return from his second knee reconstruction in three seasons, but the Saints running back's brief appearance wasn't enough to keep the Houston Texans from staying perfect in the preseason. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: New Orleans Saints vs. Houston Texans

Items.description: The Rams won 7-6 on a touchdown run by Travis Minor with all backups on the field. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: St. Louis Rams vs. San Diego Chargers

Items.description: John Vaughn, filling in for All-Pro Rob Bironas, kicked a 33-yard field goal as time expired Friday night to lift the Titans to a 17-16 victory over the Raiders in an preseason featuring the first quarterbacks taken in the 2006 and 2007 drafts. NFL Preseason
No scribbled messages on his shoulder pads this time. No trash talk, either. Just Brandon Marshall letting his play do all the debating with a silenced Adam "Pacman" Jones. NFL Preseason
J.T. O'Sullivan might have moved a step closer toward completing his long-shot bid to become the San Francisco 49ers starting quarterback. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: San Francisco 49ers vs. Green Bay Packers

Items.description: Bloodied Rex Grossman hopes this wasn't a knockout blow in his fight for the Bears' quarterback battle. NFL Preseason

Pro Bowl receiver Chad Johnson hurt his left shoulder Sunday night during the Detroit Lions' 27-10 victory over the Cincinnati Bengals, who now have their top two receivers and their starting tailback limited by injuries. NFL Preseason
No Tom Brady equals little offense for the New England Patriots this preseason. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Buccaneers vs. New England Patriots

Items.description: Eli Manning was in Super Bowl form for the New York Giants and Domenik Hixon was even better. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: New York Giants vs. Cleveland Browns

Items.description: J.T. O'Sullivan threw for 126 yards and a touchdown, and the 49ers beat the Bears 37-30 on Thursday night. NFL Preseason
Matt Ryan, making his first preseason start, opened the second half with a touchdown pass to give Atlanta the lead and the Falcons beat the Tennessee Titans 17-3 on Friday night. NFL Preseason
The New England Patriots were missing a lot more than Tom Brady, namely tackles, open receivers and a chance to leave their preseason problems behind. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: New England Patriots vs. Philadelphia Eagles

Items.description: Take away a couple of bad throws by Tony Romo, and the Dallas Cowboys finally resembled the team that everybody is expecting to see this season. NFL Preseason

Brett Favre's replacement as Green Bay quarterback bounced back from a bad game at San Francisco to complete 18 of 22 passes for 193 yards and a touchdown in the Packers' 27-24 win over Denver on Friday night. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: Denver Broncos vs. Green Bay Packers

Items.description: Brady Quinn was lackluster in his first NFL start and the depleted Cleveland Browns were roughed up for the second time in a week. NFL Preseason
The New York Giants hope they didn't lose more than just a preseason game to the New York Jets. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: New York Jets vs. New York Giants

Items.description: Jason Taylor limped off the field with a worrisome knee injury and the Redskins quickly unraveled against the Panthers' 1-2 punch of DeAngelo Williams and Jonathan Stewart. NFL Preseason
Ted Ginn Jr. is starting to look as though he's worth that high draft pick. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: Miami Dolphins vs. Kansas City Chiefs

Items.description: At least Jeff Garcia's preseason debut ended on a positive note. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Buccaneers vs. Jacksonville Jaguars

Items.description: The blood on Carson Palmer's face reflected the state of the Cincinnati Bengals' offense: a nasty, ugly mess. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: Cincinnati Bengals vs. New Orleans Saints

Items.description: Mike Tomlin has moved on, but Minnesota's defense hasn't lost its edge. NFL Preseason

Even with newly signed Steven Jackson just a spectator, the St. Louis Rams' first-string offense ended its long slump with two touchdowns.Troy Smith's illness forced the Baltimore Ravens to put their quarterback derby on hold. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: St. Louis Rams vs. Baltimore Ravens

Items.description: Matt Leinart threw three interceptions in less than two quarters before the Cardinals offense opened things up in the second half of a 24-0 victory over the Raiders on Saturday night. NFL Preseason
The Buffalo Bills ruined Indianapolis' grand opening celebration Sunday night. NFL Preseason

Backup quarterback Billy Volek threw a 2-point conversion pass to Malcom Floyd in the fourth quarter, giving the San Diego Chargers an 18-17 preseason win over the Seattle Seahawks on Monday night. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: San Diego Chargers vs. Seattle Seahawks

Items.description: Turned out the Detroit Lions' second- and third-stringers were better than the Buffalo Bills, winning 14-6 on Thursday in a game in which both teams were only interested in resting their starters for the regular season. NFL Preseason
With Brett Favre sitting out, fourth-string quarterback Erik Ainge led the New York Jets to a 27-20 victory over the Philadelphia Eagles in the preseason finale Thursday night. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: Philadelphia Eagles vs. New York Jets

Items.description: Matt Ryan used the final preseason game to get a feel for being the Atlanta Falcons starting quarterback. NFL Preseason

Packers quarterback Aaron Rodgers took the rest of the night off after throwing a touchdown pass on his first snap, and the Tennessee Titans held on to beat Green Bay 23-21 in Thursday night's preseason finale at Lambeau Field. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: Green Bay Packers vs. Tennessee Titans

Items.description: Cincinnati didn't need Carson Palmer, Chad Johnson or T.J. Houshmandzadeh on Thursday night. NFL Preseason
The Chiefs offense grabbed some much-needed momentum with a 21-17 victory over the Rams on Thursday night. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: Kansas City Chiefs vs. St. Louis Rams

Items.description: No Tom Brady. No Eli Manning. The New England Patriots and New York Giants took no chances with their quarterbacks in a preseason finale on Thursday night that matched February's Super Bowl opponents. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: New York Giants vs. New England Patriots

Items.description: Jeff Reed kicked his fourth field goal of the game and his eighth in less than a week, a 43-yarder on the last play, and the Pittsburgh Steelers beat the Carolina Panthers' backups 19-16. NFL Preseason

Gregg Williams showed up the team that let him go, his Jacksonville Jaguars defense stopping cold a Washington Redskins first-string attack that once again looked far from ready for the regular season. NFL Preseason

Brady Quinn looked better prepared for the season opener in case Derek Anderson isn't ready, leading Cleveland on two scoring drives as the Browns closed their exhibition schedule with a 16-10 loss to the Chicago Bears on Thursday night. NFL Preseason

Sam Hurd, the team's No. 3 wideout, left the locker room wearing a protective boot on his left foot Thursday night after getting hurt in the Cowboys' 16-10 victory over the Minnesota Vikings in their preseason finale. NFL Preseason
With three catches this preseason, Dexter Jackson probably isn't the receiver Tampa Bay has been looking for to play opposite Joey Galloway. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: Houston Texans vs. Tampa Bay Buccaneers

Items.description: Ronnie Brown returned from a thumb injury in good enough form to make a case for sharing carries with Ricky Williams this season. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: New Orleans Saints vs. Miami Dolphins

Items.description: Matt Leinart gained a measure of redemption in Arizona's preseason finale, even if it came against what essentially was the Denver Broncos' junior varsity. NFL Preseason
Even against his hometown team's third-stringers and scrubs, Alex Smith demonstrated why he's no longer the San Francisco 49ers' starting quarterback. NFL Preseason
Items.vs: San Francisco 49ers vs. San Diego Chargers

Items.description: The second- and third-string Seattle Seahawks were just like their starters: better than the Oakland Raiders. NFL Preseason
The New York Giants kicked off their Super Bowl title defense with what else -- defense.
Items.vs: New York Giants vs. Washington Redskins

Items.description: Matt Ryan threw for a 62-yard touchdown with his first NFL pass, Michael Turner set an Atlanta record with 220 yards rushing and the Falcons began a new era with a 34-21 victory over the Detroit Lions on Sunday.
The Baltimore Ravens received a typically solid performance from their defense in defeating the Cincinnati Bengals 17-10 Sunday.
The Buffalo Bills' special teams led them to a 34-10 victory over the Seattle Seahawks on Sunday.
Brett Favre hardly looked like the retiring type, raising his arms to signal a touchdown, then leaping and skipping to the bench, where he vaulted into the arms of two teammates.
Items.vs: Miami Dolphins vs. New York Jets

Items.description: Tom Brady limped off the field under the worried stares of Patriots fans. The thing they feared most finally happened -- losing the NFL's reigning MVP to injury.
Items.vs: New England Patriots vs. Kansas City Chiefs

Items.description: Drew Brees threw for 343 yards and three touchdowns, and Scott Fujita made a clinching interception in the final minute, lifting the New Orleans Saints to a 24-20 victory over the Tampa Bay Buccaneers on Sunday.
Items.vs: New Orleans Saints vs. Tampa Bay Buccaneers

Items.description: Donovan McNabb threw for 361 yards and three touchdowns, rookie DeSean Jackson had an impressive debut and the Eagles routed the Rams 38-3 on Sunday.
Items.vs: Philadelphia Eagles vs. St. Louis Rams

Items.description: Willie Parker and the Pittsburgh Steelers made certain the Texans didn't get a second chance in a 38-17 win that was effectively over early in the second quarter.
The Tennessee Titans sacked David Garrard seven times and Cortland Finnegan intercepted him twice in beating Jacksonville 17-10 Sunday in the season opener between the AFC's two wild cards in 2007.

Terrell Owens caught a 35-yard touchdown pass, Tony Romo effortlessly picked apart Cleveland's secondary, Marion Barber scored on a pair of 1-yard runs and the Dallas Cowboys opened the season by overwhelming the Browns 28-10 on Sunday.
Jake Delhomme threw a 14-yard touchdown pass to tight end Dante Rosaraio as time expired to lift the Carolina Panthers to a shocking 26-24 win over the Chargers on Sunday.
Items.vs: San Diego Chargers vs. Carolina Panthers

Items.description: Kurt Warner passed for 197 yards and led three monotonously effective drives in the second half of the Cardinals' 23-13 victory over the San Francisco 49ers on Sunday.

Rookie running back Matt Forte ran for 123 yards and one touchdown in his NFL debut, and Kyle Orton committed no turnovers as the Bears surprised the Indianapolis Colts 29-13 at the first regular-season game played at Lucas Oil Stadium.

Aaron Rodgers passed his first test as the Green Bay Packers' new quarterback, throwing for 178 yards and a touchdown and scoring on a game-clinching sneak in a 24-19 victory over the Minnesota Vikings on Monday night.
Items.vs: Green Bay Packers vs. Minnesota Vikings

Items.description: Jay Cutler threw for 300 yards with long touchdown passes to rookie Eddie Royal and Darrell Jackson that helped the Denver Broncos beat up on their AFC West rivals in a 41-14 victory over the Oakland Raiders on Monday night.
After watching the Chicago Bears build a big lead behind a stout defense and a rookie running back, the Carolina Panthers used the same combination to stage a late comeback for an unlikely 2-0 start.

Backup quarterback Kerry Collins threw low, tight passes that stayed on track in Cincinnati's wind-tunnel of a stadium Sunday, setting up a 24-7 victory that kept the Tennessee Titans unbeaten and brought them a little relief at the end of a trying week.
Aaron Rodgers threw three touchdown passes in the first four drives of his second start, helping Green Bay build a big lead it needed in a 48-25 win over the Detroit Lions on Sunday.
Items.vs: Detroit Lions vs. Green Bay Packers

Items.description: Trent Edwards was good early and even better late, doing just enough to lead the Buffalo Bills to their best start in five years.

Rookie Darren McFadden ran for 164 yards and a touchdown and Sebastian Janikowski kicked a team-record 56-yard field goal, leading the Raiders to a 23-8 victory Sunday over an inept Chiefs team that tried three quarterbacks.
Items.vs: Kansas City Chiefs vs. Oakland Raiders

Items.description: Taking a beating all afternoon, Peyton Manning peeled himself off the Metrodome turf and gave it right back to the Minnesota defense.
Eli Manning threw three touchdown passes and the New York Giants sacked Marc Bulger five times while limiting the St. Louis Rams to a fluke touchdown in a 41-13 victory on Sunday.
Items.vs: St. Louis Rams vs. New York Giants

Items.description: Jason Campbell went from uncomfortable to prolific, completing 24 of 36 passes for 321 yards in a 29-24 victory over the New Orleans Saints.
Items.vs: Washington Redskins vs. New Orleans Saints

Items.description: Joe Nedney shook off a missed field goal as time expired in regulation and kicked a 40-yarder 4:40 into overtime Sunday, sending the San Francisco 49ers past the Seattle Seahawks 33-30.
Two early mistakes by Matt Ryan was all it took to dig a hole the Atlanta Falcons couldn't escape against the Tampa Bay Buccaneers.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Buccaneers vs. Atlanta Falcons

Items.description: Kurt Warner looked like he did in his MVP days, Anquan Boldin certainly wasn't sulking over contract woes, and Larry Fitzgerald caught almost everything thrown his way. The result was a 31-10 Arizona rout of the Miami Dolphins on Sunday.

Playing with house money, Mike Shanahan went for the 2-point conversion with 29 seconds left and Jay Cutler hit rookie Eddie Royal over the middle to give the Denver Broncos a 39-38 win over the stunned San Diego Chargers on Sunday.
Items.vs: Denver Broncos vs. San Diego Chargers

Items.description: Life without Tom Brady might not be so bad for New England after all.
Items.vs: New York Jets vs. New England Patriots

Items.description: Ignoring his sore right shoulder and wind gusts of 60 mph, Ben Roethlisberger threw an 11-yard touchdown pass to Hines Ward as the Pittsburgh Steelers made it 10 straight wins over their closest rivals, beating the Cleveland Browns 10-6 on Sunday.
Terrell Owens caught the long pass in stride, cruised into the end zone and began showing off.
Michael Turner ran for three touchdowns and the Atlanta Falcons scored the first 24 points to beat Kansas City 38-14 on Sunday, giving the Chiefs their 12th straight loss.
Items.vs: Atlanta Falcons vs. Kansas City Chiefs

Items.description: Bills 24, Raiders 23
Brian Griese set up Matt Bryant's winning 21-yard field goal in overtime with a 38-yard pass to Antonio Bryant, and the Buccaneers rallied to beat the Bears 27-24 on Sunday.
Items.vs: Chicago Bears vs. Tampa Bay Buccaneers

Items.description: Gus Frerotte stabilized Minnesota's wobbly passing attack for at least one week, after Antoine Winfield and the rest of defense propped it up once again.
Ronnie Brown and the lowly Miami Dolphins ended the Patriots' record winning streak and made New England's defense look as shaky as its Tom Brady-less offense Sunday.
Items.vs: New England Patriots vs. Miami Dolphins

Items.description: The New York Giants are off to their best start since 2000, and a late play that was not reviewed in overtime may have helped.
Items.vs: New York Giants vs. Cincinnati Bengals

Items.description: The Tennessee Titans remained perfect in their best start since their lone Super Bowl appearance. The Houston Texans? Well, at least they got back on a football field.

Carlos Rogers' 42-yard interception return of a tipped pass set up the go-ahead touchdown early in the fourth quarter Sunday, and the Washington Redskins controlled the rest of the game for a 24-17 victory over the Arizona Cardinals.
Martin Gramatica's 43-yard field goal try with 1:55 remaining was wide right, and the Denver Broncos escaped with a 34-32 win over the New Orleans Saints on Sunday.
Items.vs: Denver Broncos vs. New Orleans Saints

Items.description: The Detroit Lions thought Mike Martz was part of the problem. So far in San Francisco, the offensive mastermind has been the solution for the 49ers' years of offensive awfulness.
All the ailing, winless Seattle Seahawks needed was everyone's cure-all, a visit from the St. Louis Rams.
Items.vs: Seattle Seahawks vs. St. Louis Rams

Items.description: In less than a minute, the Baltimore Ravens to scored two touchdowns and further ruined an already agonizing season for the Cleveland Browns.

After wearing out the Indy defense on the ground, Josh Scobee saved the game -- and perhaps the season -- by making a 51-yard field goal with 4 seconds left to give the Jaguars a 23-21 victory, their first in Indy since 2004.
A swarming D had nine sacks, forced a safety and got three turnovers, and the Philadelphia Eagles beat the Pittsburgh Steelers 15-6 Sunday.

On an uncharacteristically quiet night for Terrell Owens, the Dallas Cowboys leaned on their defense and running game -- then unleashed little-known wide receiver Miles Austin to put away a 27-16 victory over the Green Bay Packers on Sunday night.
Items.vs: Green Bay Packers vs. Dallas Cowboys

Items.description: Philip Rivers and LaDainian Tomlinson led the Chargers past Brett Favre and the Jets on Monday.
Items.vs: San Diego Chargers vs. New York Jets

Items.description: Steve Smith's first touchdown following his two-game suspension was part of a dominating day as the cohesive Carolina Panthers beat the Atlanta Falcons 24-9 on Sunday.
Derek Anderson's one good moment was enough to save the Cleveland Browns' season. Maybe his job, too.
Josh Scobee won a second straight game for the Jacksonville Jaguars, with plenty of help from David Garrard again.
Larry Johnson ran for 198 yards and two touchdowns and the Chiefs took advantage of four Denver turnovers for a 33-19 victory Sunday over the previously unbeaten Broncos.
Items.vs: Kansas City Chiefs vs. Denver Broncos

Items.description: New Orleans running back Deuce McAllister gained 83 yards, converting key third downs and scoring his first touchdown, and the Saints beat the San Francisco 49ers 31-17 on Sunday.
Items.vs: New Orleans Saints vs. San Francisco 49ers

Items.description: The New York Jets' defense rattled and roughed up Kurt Warner in the second quarter, and Brett Favre took care of the rest.
Items.vs: New York Jets vs. Arizona Cardinals

Items.description: Derrick Brooks had one of three interceptions off the Green Bay quarterback and also forced a fumble that Jermaine Phillips returned 38 yards for a touchdown Sunday, helping the Bucs beat the Packers 30-21.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Buccaneers vs. Green Bay Packers

Items.description: Rookie Chris Johnson scored two touchdowns and the defense forced four turnovers that the Titans turned into 21 points as Tennessee beat the Minnesota Vikings 30-17 Sunday. The Titans improved to 4-0 for the first time in franchise history.
Another blown fourth-quarter lead for Oakland led to yet another San Diego win over the Raiders and the possible end of coach Lane Kiffin's tenure.
Items.vs: Oakland Raiders vs. San Diego Chargers

Items.description: For the first time in 16 years, the Buffalo Bills are 4-0. Unlike the previous two weeks, there was no need for late-game heroics to keep them unbeaten.
Items.vs: St. Louis Rams vs. Buffalo Bills

Items.description: New Washington Redskins coach Jim Zorn was looking for something to help him build up a healthy dose of hate for the Dallas Cowboys. Turns out, he kinds of likes playing his team's archrival.

Alex Brown stopped Correll Buckhalter at the goal line late in the game, and Chicago hung on to beat the Philadelphia Eagles 24-20 Sunday night after head-scratching losses that raised questions about their killer instinct.
Jeff Reed kicked a 46-yard field goal in overtime and the Pittsburgh Steelers overcame a 10-point deficit, numerous injuries and a late Baltimore comeback to outlast the Ravens 23-20 on Monday night.
The Tennessee Titans are still unbeaten, thanks to a late touchdown drive and a defense that outperformed the top-ranked unit in the league.
Forgive Herm Edwards if he may want to avoid his old college buddy from now on. Every time he coaches against John Fox, he's had the Carolina Panthers playing their best.
Items.vs: Carolina Panthers vs. Kansas City Chiefs

Items.description: Like many NFL players, Kyle Orton seems to love playing the Detroit Lions.
Aaron Rodgers played hurt and played hard. But he was upstaged by Matt Ryan and the Atlanta Falcons.
Items.vs: Green Bay Packers vs. Atlanta Falcons

Items.description: The Indianapolis Colts scored 21 points in 31⁄2 minutes late in Sunday's game, rallying past the stunned Houston Texans 31-27.
The Miami Dolphins are winning the old-fashioned way. The single wing helped build a lead, and a goal-line stand preserved it.
Items.vs: Miami Dolphins vs. San Diego Chargers

Items.description: In a nearly flawless performance, Eli Manning threw two touchdowns, Brandon Jacobs ran for two more and the unbeaten Giants scored on their first five possessions in a 44-6 victory that embarrassed the Seattle Seahawks on Sunday.
Items.vs: New York Giants vs. Seattle Seahawks

Items.description: Another road win against a division opponent has the Washington Redskins in perfect position to make a run at the NFC East.
Jay Cutler guided a patient Denver offense to a 16-13 win over the Tampa Bay Buccaneers, who lost their starting quarterback on a cornerback blitz in the third quarter.
Items.vs: Denver Broncos vs. Tampa Bay Buccaneers

Items.description: The Buffalo Bills lost their quarterback and, emphatically, their first game of the season.
When the pass went through Miles Austin's hands at the 1 and into Patrick Crayton's hands in the end zone, everyone on the Dallas Cowboys was smiling and laughing.
From Randy Moss' dynamic 66-yard touchdown catch to Kevin Faulk's score on a direct snap, the New England Patriots returned to their usual regular-season form in an unusual place.
Items.vs: San Francisco 49ers vs. New England Patriots

Items.description: Ben Roethlisberger threw for 309 yards and three touchdowns, helping the Steelers overcome their offensive woes and leading them to a 26-21 victory over the Jacksonville Jaguars on Sunday night.

Ryan Longwell's 30-yard field goal with 13 seconds left lifted the Minnesota Vikings to a 30-27 comeback victory over the New Orleans Saints on Monday night, spoiling a record-tying performance by Reggie Bush.
Items.vs: New Orleans Saints vs. Minnesota Vikings

Items.description: Making up for a miss just minutes earlier, Jason Elam kicked a 48-yard field goal on the final play, giving the Atlanta Falcons an improbable 22-20 victory over the Chicago Bears on Sunday.
Matt Schaub threw interceptions on Houston's first two possessions, but ran for a 3-yard touchdown with 3 seconds left, leading the Texans to a 29-28 victory over the Miami Dolphins on Sunday.

Peyton Manning threw two touchdown passes to Marvin Harrison, a third to Reggie Wayne, and the Colts sputtering offense finally got itself righted Sunday, routing the Baltimore Ravens' top-ranked defense 31-3.

A questionable pass interference penalty on Leigh Bodden put Minnesota's woeful offense in position for a 26-yard field goal by Ryan Longwell with 9 seconds to go that lifted the Vikings to a 12-10 victory Sunday, keeping the Lions winless on the season.
Connecting on 87 percent of his throws, Brees passed for 320 yards and three touchdowns, and the New Orleans Saints routed the Oakland Raiders 34-3 Sunday.
Items.vs: New Orleans Saints vs. Oakland Raiders

Items.description: Rested and rusty after a bye week, the New York Jets made just enough plays to beat the winless Cincinnati Bengals.
Items.vs: New York Jets vs. Cincinnati Bengals

Items.description: Jeff Garcia delivered exactly what the Bucs were looking for in a 27-3 victory over the Panthers on Sunday.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Buccaneers vs. Carolina Panthers

Items.description: Josh Brown kicked a 49-yard field goal on the last play of the game Sunday, giving the St. Louis Rams a 19-17 upset of the Washington Redskins.
Items.vs: Washington Redskins vs. St. Louis Rams

Items.description: The Jaguars got superb performances from quarterback David Garrard and running back Maurice Jones-Drew, plus three takeaways by their defense in a 24-17 win over the bumbling Broncos.
Sean Morey blocked Mat McBriar's punt and Monty Beisel scooped up the ball and scored from 3 yards to give the Cardinals a crazy 30-24 overtime victory over the Cowboys on Sunday.
Donovan McNabb and the Philadelphia defense wouldn't allow a bizarre blocked field goal to ruin an otherwise dominant day.
Aaron Rodgers again ignored pain. He heaped it on the sinking Seahawks instead.
Items.vs: Seattle Seahawks vs. Green Bay Packers

Items.description: Philip Rivers and the San Diego Chargers solved their Patriots problem and perhaps saved their season.
Items.vs: San Diego Chargers vs. New England Patriots

Items.description: The Cleveland Browns may have flipped around their season.
Items.vs: Cleveland Browns vs. New York Giants

Items.description: After the power went out at Ralph Wilson Stadium, Trent Edwards and Kawika Mitchell provided all the electricity the Buffalo Bills needed against the San Diego Chargers.
Items.vs: Buffalo Bills vs. San Diego Chargers

Items.description: A week after giving up sole possession of first place in the NFC South with a woeful road performance, the Panthers were dominant again at home.
Items.vs: Carolina Panthers vs. New Orleans Saints

Items.description: Kyle Orton threw two touchdown passes, special teams chipped in with two more and the Bears hung on for a 48-41 victory over the Minnesota Vikings on Sunday.
Mewelde Moore got into the end zone three times. The Pittsburgh Steelers defense got to the quarterback seven times. Perfect math against a bad team.

LenDale White rushed for three touchdowns and 149 yards, including an 80-yard sprint, and Chris Johnson unfurled a 66-yard gallop while rushing for 168 yards to help Tennessee cruise past the punchless Chiefs 34-10 Sunday.
Items.vs: Kansas City Chiefs vs. Tennessee Titans

Items.description: Cam Cameron's play-calling worked better Sunday than it did last year in Miami.
Who cares that the New York Giants' run on the road is over? The Super Bowl champions are winning at home this year.
Items.vs: New York Giants vs. San Francisco 49ers

Items.description: Steven Jackson ran for 160 yards on 25 carries with three touchdowns and the Rams beat the Cowboys 34-14 on Sunday.
Items.vs: St. Louis Rams vs. Dallas Cowboys

Items.description: The Houston Texans had such a good start it made up for their sloppy finish.
The Packers rediscovered their swagger in a 34-14 victory over the Colts on Sunday.
Items.vs: Green Bay Packers vs. Indianapolis Colts

Items.description: Sebastian Janikowski bailed out Oakland coach Tom Cable in his home debut as Raiders coach.
Items.vs: Oakland Raiders vs. New York Jets

Items.description: For 21⁄2 quarters, the Washington Redskins and Cleveland Browns produced lots of punts and no points.
Jeff Garcia was a Pro Bowl quarterback last season. He played like one again Sunday night.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Buccaneers vs. Seattle Seahawks

Items.description: Matt Cassel threw three touchdown passes in his best game since taking over for the injured quarterback, Sammy Morris rushed for 138 yards and New England routed the Denver Broncos 41-7 Monday night.
Items.vs: New England Patriots vs. Denver Broncos

Items.description: Baltimore limited the Raiders to 35 yards while building a 19-point halftime lead en route to 29-10 victory Sunday.
On the day the NFL played in Europe, two former Amsterdam Admirals teammates put on a quarterbacking clinic stateside.
Brad Johnson's aim was off and the boo birds were roaring at Texas Stadium. Somehow, the Dallas Cowboys pulled out of their midseason slump anyway.
Items.vs: Dallas Cowboys vs. Tampa Bay Buccaneers

Items.description: Santana Moss had a go-ahead touchdown reception in the third quarter and returned a punt for another score in the fourth, lifting the Washington Redskins to a 25-17 victory over the winless Lions on Sunday.
Change those labels: Ted Ginn Jr. is no longer a draft bust, and the Miami Dolphins are much better than dreadful.
Short-handed but sure-handed, the New England Patriots got by the St. Louis Rams on a fingertip touchdown catch by Kevin Faulk.
Items.vs: New England Patriots vs. St. Louis Rams

Items.description: A trans-Atlantic trip was just what Drew Brees and the New Orleans Saints needed to get their season back on track.
Items.vs: New Orleans Saints vs. San Diego Chargers

Items.description: After struggling all game, Brett Favre connected with Laveranues Coles for a 15-yard touchdown pass with 1 minute left as the New York Jets escaped with a 28-24 victory over the Kansas City Chiefs on Sunday.
Items.vs: New York Jets vs. Kansas City Chiefs

Items.description: Brian Westbrook returned to his All-Pro form and rushed for 167 yards and two touchdowns as part of a dynamic all-around effort, and the Eagles beat the Falcons 27-14 on Sunday.
In his first meeting against his former team, Kevin Walter scored two touchdowns to lead the Houston Texans to a 35-6 victory over the winless Bengals on Sunday.
Jamal Lewis ran for 81 yards and a touchdown, Derek Anderson completed three huge passes and the Browns beat the Jacksonville Jaguars 23-17 Sunday.
Linebacker James Harrison's high snap on the punt gave New York two points, and the Giants held off Pittsburgh for a 21-14 victory in a matchup of division leaders.
Items.vs: Pittsburgh Steelers vs. New York Giants

Items.description: Compared to new coach Mike Singletary's feuding, fumbling, quarterback-switching 49ers, even the struggling Seattle Seahawks looked sharp.
LenDale White ran for two touchdowns, Chris Hope intercepted Manning twice and the Titans routed the Indianapolis Colts 31-21 Monday night.
Abram Elam and the New York Jets' defense made Brett Favre's job easy, negating the need for any late-game comebacks. And suddenly, the AFC East race is a whole lot tighter.
Items.vs: Buffalo Bills vs. New York Jets

Items.description: Rex Grossman dove into the end zone, then ran to the side and spiked the ball. He had something to celebrate and the Chicago Bears had reason to exhale.
Ryan Fitzpatrick threw a pair of touchdown passes to Chad Ocho Cinco and Cincinnati stopped a late two-point conversion try Sunday, preserving a 21-19 victory over the stunned Jacksonville Jaguars.
Baltimore's rookies came through and the Ravens' old man kicked it in, too.
Jeff Garcia's 24-yard touchdown pass and 2-point conversion toss tied it with 19 seconds left and Matt Bryant's 33-yard field goal in overtime gave the Buccaneers a 30-27 win over the Chiefs.
Items.vs: Kansas City Chiefs vs. Tampa Bay Buccaneers

Items.description: Andre Johnson was silenced until the very end, and Houston's winning streak ended with a harsh welcome by Adrian Peterson's might and Minnesota's defense.
Arizona's 24-point second quarter took the fight out of the St. Louis Rams.
Items.vs: St. Louis Rams vs. Arizona Cardinals

Items.description: Rob Bironas got a second chance at redemption in overtime, kicking a 41-yard field goal with 9:36 to go that kept the Titans the NFL's last unbeaten team with a 19-16 victory over the Green Bay Packers on Sunday.
Items.vs: Tennessee Titans vs. Green Bay Packers

Items.description: The Miami Dolphins bottled up Denver's ground game and intercepted Jay Cutler three times in a 26-17 win over the befuddled Broncos on Sunday.
Eli Manning threw three touchdown passes, Brandon Jacobs rushed for 117 yards and a score and the Giants defense took advantage of Tony Romo's absence to intercept three passes in a 35-14 victory.
Items.vs: New York Giants vs. Dallas Cowboys

Items.description: Even in the depths of the Michael Vick- and Bobby Petrino-inspired despair last year in Atlanta, the Falcons never sank as low as they sent the Oakland Raiders on Sunday.
Donovan McNabb rebounded from early problems to complete 28 of 43 passes for 349 yards and two touchdowns to rally the Eagles to a 26-7 victory over the swooning Seahawks on Sunday.
Adam Vinatieri showed New England he's still the NFL's best clutch kicker.
Items.vs: Indianapolis Colts vs. New England Patriots

Items.description: Byron Leftwich led two touchdown drives after Ben Roethlisberger reinjured his throwing shoulder and the Pittsburgh Steelers beat the Washington Redskins 23-6 on Monday night.
Jay Cutler turned Brady Quinn's big night into his own prime-time showcase.
Drew Brees was the NFL's most prolific passer. He was no match for the Falcons' defense.
Items.vs: Atlanta Falcons vs. New Orleans Saints

Items.description: LenDale White and Chris Johnson kept getting hit for losses. The Tennessee Titans refused to take a bigger one, though, and now they're 9-0.
The Jacksonville Jaguars got back to their winning formula of relying on their efficient quarterback and tandem of running backs.
Joe Flacco is making a team known for defense look pretty potent on offense.
The Dolphins' sizable bag of tricks saved them on a day the offense sputtered, and they withstood a frantic rally by injury-riddled Seattle to win 21-19 Sunday.
Ending the Vikings' five-game losing streak to the Packers, Adrian Peterson rushed for 192 yards and reached across the end zone with 2:22 left to lift Minnesota to a 28-27 victory on Sunday.
Items.vs: Minnesota Vikings vs. Green Bay Packers

Items.description: Patriots rookie runner BenJarvus Green-Ellis had his best game as a pro, Matt Cassel had a solid one and the free-falling Bills had another bad one.
Items.vs: New England Patriots vs. Buffalo Bills

Items.description: The dominant New York Jets took advantage of every mistake by the St. Louis Rams, making their 47-3 rout look more like a scrimmage than an NFL game.
Items.vs: New York Jets vs. St. Louis Rams

Items.description: Even the worst game of Jake Delhomme's career proved to be enough to beat the lowly Oakland Raiders.
his time, the Indianapolis Colts completed the comeback against the Pittsburgh Steelers.
Clinton Hart and the San Diego Chargers avoided the kind of upset that really could have ruined their season.
Items.vs: San Diego Chargers vs. Kansas City Chiefs

Items.description: Eli Manning threw two touchdown passes, Brandon Jacobs had two TD runs and the Giants held on to beat the Philadelphia Eagles 36-31 and further distance themselves from the pack in the NFL's toughest division.
Items.vs: Philadelphia Eagles vs. New York Giants

Items.description: The Cardinals stopped Michael Robinson up the middle from the 2-yard line as the game ended Monday night to preserve a 29-24 victory over the San Francisco 49ers.

Jay Feely kicked a 34-yard field goal on the first series of overtime after New England tied the game on Matt Cassel's pass to Randy Moss with :01 left in regulation and the Jets survived a Tom Brady-like comeback with a 34-31 victory Thursday night.
Items.vs: New England Patriots vs. New York Jets

Items.description: Denver pulled out every trick to deal with a rash of injuries, even starting a player on both offense and defense, to beat the surprising Falcons 24-20 on Sunday.

The one-two punch of DeAngelo Williams and Jonathan Stewart dazzled with a record setting day on the ground for Carolina. The Panthers needed all those yards to squeak by the league's only winless team.
The Eagles and Bengals played to a 13-13 tie on Sunday, the NFL's first in six years.
Ryan Grant finally hit his stride for the Green Bay Packers, rushing for 145 yards and a touchdown in a dominant 37-3 victory over the Chicago Bears on Sunday.
Items.vs: Green Bay Packers vs. Chicago Bears

Items.description: Peyton Manning led Indianapolis on four straight scoring drives in the second half, wiping out two Houston leads and giving the Colts a badly needed 33-27 victory Sunday.
It only took a trip to Kansas City for the New Orleans Saints to end their winless streak on the road.
Items.vs: Kansas City Chiefs vs. New Orleans Saints

Items.description: Dan Carpenter nailed a 38-yard field goal with 38 seconds left to cap a 61-yard drive, and the Dolphins earned their fourth consecutive victory Sunday, beating woeful Oakland 17-15.
The Super Bowl champion New York Giants are running over opponents. Not even Ray Lewis and the Baltimore Ravens' league-best rushing defense could avoid becoming the latest victims.
Items.vs: New York Giants vs. Baltimore Ravens

Items.description: The Bucs defeat the Vikings 19-13 on Sunday.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Buccaneers vs. Minnesota Vikings

Items.description: Shaun Hill and the San Francisco 49ers' beleaguered offense clicked for just one quarter. Still, those 15 minutes were more than enough time to bury the miserable St. Louis Rams.
Items.vs: San Francisco 49ers vs. St. Louis Rams

Items.description: This Cardinals' surge of rewriting their sorry history has now written off Seattle.
Kerry Collins threw three touchdown passes, Albert Haynesworth dominated defensively again and the Titans improved to 10-0 with a 24-14 victory over the Jacksonville Jaguars on Sunday.
The only thing perfect on a snowy, frigid day when the weather and the offenses were equally awful was San Diego's regular-season record in Pittsburgh.
Items.vs: Pittsburgh Steelers vs. San Diego Chargers

Items.description: Tony Romo celebrated the go-ahead touchdown pass by bouncing up and down like a little kid and patting teammates on the back with his left hand, carefully avoiding any further damage to his heavily wrapped right pinkie.
Phil Dawson capped a five field-goal outing by hitting a career-long 56-yarder with 1:39 remaining to secure the Browns' 29-27 win over the reeling Bills on Monday night.
Ben Roethlisberger and the Pittsburgh Steelers know exactly how to beat the Cincinnati Bengals -- with or without Chad Ocho Cinco.
Donovan McNabb was pulled from the Eagles blowout loss to the Ravens on Sunday.
Picked apart by Houston quarterback Sage Rosenfels and unable to do anything once they had the ball, the Browns were humiliated in a 16-6 loss on Sunday to the Texans.
Terrell Owens had over 200 yards receiving and the Cowboys beat the Niners on Sunday.
The Buccaneers overcame a 17-point deficit to keep the Lions winless.
Items.vs: Detroit Lions vs. Tampa Bay Buccaneers

Items.description: Adrian Peterson came back from a benching to help the Vikings beat the Jaguars.

A mistake-free Trent Edwards threw for two touchdowns and ran for two more and the Bills romped past Kansas City 54-31 Sunday, breaking a four-game losing streak while scoring more points than anyone ever scored before against the Chiefs.
Items.vs: Kansas City Chiefs vs. Buffalo Bills

Items.description: Matt Cassel threw for 415 yards and the Patriots beat the Dolphins on Sunday.
Items.vs: Miami Dolphins vs. New England Patriots

Items.description: Matt Forte's big rushing day helped the Bears rout the hapless Rams.
Items.vs: St. Louis Rams vs. Chicago Bears

Items.description: Brett Favre and the Jets handed the Titans their first loss of the season.
Items.vs: Tennessee Titans vs. New York Jets

Items.description: Ashley Lelie helped the Raiders beat his old team, the Broncos, on Sunday.
The Giants escaped the Cardinals on Sunday night.
Items.vs: Arizona Cardinals vs. New York Giants

Items.description: Michael Turner's four rushing touchdowns carried the Falcons over the Panthers on Sunday.
Clinton Portis gained 143 yards on 29 carries, including key runs late that helped preserve the Redskins' first victory in almost a month, 20-17 over the Seattle Seahawks.

Adam Vinatieri, one of the most clutch kickers in NFL history, made a 51-yard field goal as time expired to lift Peyton Manning and the Indianapolis Colts to a heart-stopping 23-20 win over the San Diego Chargers on Sunday night.
Items.vs: San Diego Chargers vs. Indianapolis Colts

Items.description: Drew Brees threw for four scores, Deuce McAllister set a Saints record with his 54th career touchdown and New Orleans rolled to a 51-29 victory over the Green Bay Packers on Monday night.
Items.vs: New Orleans Saints vs. Green Bay Packers

Items.description: Chris Johnson was untouched on a short run to the outside and a long gain up the middle.
Tony Romo crisply guided Dallas to touchdowns on its first three drives and points on the first four, then turned the early surge into a 34-9 victory over the Seattle Seahawks on Thursday.
Donovan McNabb threw four touchdown passes, Brian Westbrook tied a team-record with four scores and the Philadelphia Eagles beat the Arizona Cardinals 48-20 on Thursday night.
For a 49ers team that didn't have much to play for, linebacker Patrick Willis and a suddenly sturdy San Francisco defense certainly did their job as spoilers.
Mark Clayton put a little sizzle into Baltimore's steadily evolving offense.
Often overlooked and always overshadowed by their star-studded offense, the Indianapolis Colts' defense found the end zone on a day Peyton Manning couldn't.

DeAngelo Williams scored his fourth touchdown of the game with 1:30 left on the clock, giving the Carolina Panthers a stunning come-from-behind 35-31 victory over the Green Bay Packers in wintry conditions at Lambeau Field on Sunday.
Items.vs: Green Bay Packers vs. Carolina Panthers

Items.description: The Miami Dolphins kept the St. Louis Rams out of the end zone, even with Steven Jackson back in the lineup.
Items.vs: St. Louis Rams vs. Miami Dolphins

Items.description: Jermaine Phillips and Phillip Buchanon intercepted the NFL's leading passer in the closing minutes and Matt Bryant kicked a 37-yard field goal with 1:55 remaining Sunday to help the Bucs stay atop the NFC South with a 23-20 victory over the Saints.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Buccaneers vs. New Orleans Saints

Items.description: Nothing is stopping the New York Giants these days. Not the latest distraction surrounding their star receiver. Not the rain on a dreary day in the mid-Atlantic. Not a Washington Redskins team with the NFL's leading rusher and a usually stout defense.
Items.vs: Washington Redskins vs. New York Giants

Items.description: Matt Ryan threw two touchdown passes and Michael Turner, LaDainian Tomlinson's former understudy, ran for 120 yards against his former team to lead the Falcons to a 22-16 win over the reeling Chargers on Sunday.
Items.vs: San Diego Chargers vs. Atlanta Falcons

Items.description: Pittsburgh's NFL-best defense stopped Matt Cassel's two-game offensive surge and pushed New England closer to strange territory: a sideline seat for the playoffs.
Items.vs: New England Patriots vs. Pittsburgh Steelers

Items.description: Jay Cutler and the Denver Broncos stopped the surging New York Jets 34-17, and showed they might also be a team to reckon with in the wide-open AFC.
Items.vs: New York Jets vs. Denver Broncos

Items.description: Tyler Thigpen put together one effective drive for Kansas City to beat the Oakland Raiders in a matchup between two of the NFL's worst teams.
Items.vs: Oakland Raiders vs. Kansas City Chiefs

Items.description: Bernard Berrian pulled in a 99-yard touchdown pass from Gus Frerotte that sent the Vikings to a 34-14 victory over the Bears and sole possession of the division lead Sunday night.
Mario Williams had a season-high three sacks and forced a fumble and Steve Slaton ran for a pair of touchdowns to lead the Texans to a 30-17 win over the Jaguars.

LaDainian Tomlinson scored on a 3-yard run against his favorite punching bag and Philip Rivers threw three touchdown passes, including a 59-yarder to Vincent Jackson, to give the Chargers a 34-7 victory against the Oakland Raiders on Thursday night.
Items.vs: San Diego Chargers vs. Oakland Raiders

Items.description: The Chicago Bears needed help after a brutal loss. Lucky for them the reeling Jacksonville Jaguars were in town.
Tarvaris Jackson threw a go-ahead touchdown pass early in the fourth quarter and the Minnesota Vikings held on for a 20-16 victory over the winless Lions on Sunday.

Playing his first game in a month because of a knee injury, quarterback Matt Schaub marched the Houston Texans to set up Kris Brown's 40-yard field goal on the final play of the game to beat the Green Bay Packers 24-21 on Sunday.
Items.vs: Green Bay Packers vs. Houston Texans

Items.description: Peyton Manning threw for three touchdowns, Dominic Rhodes ran for one and cornerback Kelvin Hayden's interception return produced another as the Colts routed Cincinnati 35-3 on Sunday.
Pierre Thomas rushed for 102 yards and scored two touchdowns, and the New Orleans Saints kept alive their slim playoff hopes with a 29-25 victory over NFC South rival Atlanta on Sunday.
Items.vs: New Orleans Saints vs. Atlanta Falcons

Items.description: The New York Giants finally found a bigger distraction than Plaxico Burress: Donovan McNabb, Brian Westbrook and the desperate Philadelphia Eagles.
Items.vs: New York Giants vs. Philadelphia Eagles

Items.description: The AFC South title belongs to the Tennessee Titans for the first time since 2002 in what they hope is the first of many goals reached this season.
Chad Pennington and the Miami Dolphins took advantage of an indifferent Bills "home" crowd, an inept Buffalo offense and the cozy indoors of the Rogers Centre to stay firmly in playoff contention.
The Denver Broncos keep losing players, but finally found a way to win at home.
Items.vs: Denver Broncos vs. Kansas City Chiefs

Items.description: Shaun Hill passed for 285 yards and two touchdowns against New York's porous secondary, and the 49ers sent the AFC East-leading Jets to their second straight embarrassing loss, 24-14 Sunday.
Items.vs: San Francisco 49ers vs. New York Jets

Items.description: The Patriots rallied past the Seahawks 24-21 on Sunday.
Items.vs: Seattle Seahawks vs. New England Patriots

Items.description: Kurt Warner threw for 279 yards, the defense scored twice and the Cardinals clinched their first division title in 33 years by beating the woeful St. Louis Rams 34-10 on Sunday.
Items.vs: Arizona Cardinals vs. St. Louis Rams

Items.description: Deshea Townsend scored on a 26-yard interception return with 1:40 remaining as the Steelers scored their only two touchdowns 24 seconds apart to rally from a 10-point deficit in the fourth quarter and deal the Cowboys a potentially damaging loss.
Given their uneven performance against the Baltimore Ravens, the Washington Redskins must be glad they don't face their so-called rivals on a regular basis.
DeAngelo Williams and Jonathan Stewart run over the Buccaneers and the Panthers seize control of the NFC South with a 38-23 win.
Items.vs: Carolina Panthers vs. Tampa Bay Buccaneers

Items.description: Robbie Gould and the Chicago Bears handed Drew Brees and the New Orleans Saints another devastating loss at Soldier Field.
Items.vs: Chicago Bears vs. New Orleans Saints

Items.description: Michael Turner ran for 152 yards, John Abraham had three sacks and Jason Elam kicked a 34-yard field goal in overtime to give the Atlanta Falcons a crucial 13-10 win over the Tampa Bay Buccaneers on Sunday.
Items.vs: Atlanta Falcons vs. Tampa Bay Buccaneers

Items.description: Ryan Fitzpatrick ran for a touchdown and threw for another, leading the Bengals to a 20-13 victory that ended Washington's week of grousing.
Andre Johnson had a career-high 207 yards and a touchdown to lead the Texans to their fourth consecutive win, a 13-12 victory over the Titans.
The Lions, seemingly on their way to the first 0-16 season in NFL history, were victimized in the fourth quarter by Peyton Manning and the Colts, falling 31-21.
Green Bay's slim playoff chances ended in fitting fashion -- with another fourth-quarter collapse.
Items.vs: Jacksonville Jaguars vs. Green Bay Packers

Items.description: Philip Rivers rallied San Diego from a 21-3 third-quarter deficit, throwing two touchdown passes in the final 73 seconds, and the Chargers stunned Kansas City 22-21 on Sunday.
Items.vs: Kansas City Chiefs vs. San Diego Chargers

Items.description: Miami had possession for less than 22 minutes Sunday, but held the opposition without a touchdown for the third game in a row and helped its playoff chances by beating San Francisco 14-9.
The Jets' defense was battered all game, with the Buffalo Bills primed for an upset. One big hit and one favorable bounce kept New York in control of its playoff destiny.
Items.vs: New York Jets vs. Buffalo Bills

Items.description: The Seattle Seahawks tied the game on T.J. Duckett's 1-yard run with 2:47 to go and then won it on Olindo Mare's 27-yard field goal as time expired for a 23-20 victory over the St. Louis Rams on Sunday.
Items.vs: St. Louis Rams vs. Seattle Seahawks

Items.description: Playing in place of injured Gus Frerotte, Tavaris Jackson threw for four touchdowns and the Minnesota Vikings beat NFC West champion Arizona 35-14 to stay alone atop the NFC North.
The Steelers used a second straight fourth-quarter comeback to earn another AFC North title.
In front of their ailing owner, the Carolina Panthers finished off a perfect regular season at home with a dominating performance that had to make Jerry Richardson proud.

Randy Moss pointed to his name on the back of his jersey after each touchdown catch, as if he needed to introduce himself to the fans who rarely saw that kind of performance in his two seasons in Oakland.
Items.vs: Oakland Raiders vs. New England Patriots

Items.description: The soap opera that is the Dallas Cowboys' offense gets all the attention. The defense, however, is keeping them in the playoff hunt.
Items.vs: Dallas Cowboys vs. New York Giants

Items.description: Donovan McNabb threw for 290 yards and two touchdowns, Asante Samuel scored on an interception return and the Eagles beat the struggling Cleveland Browns 30-10 for their third straight victory.
Peyton Manning was nearly perfect, exactly what the Indianapolis Colts needed to overcome all the emotion the Jacksonville Jaguars got from Richard Collier's return.
The Ravens topped the Cowboys 33-24 Saturday night in a game both teams needed to boost their playoff chances.
As bad as they've been, the Cincinnati Bengals can brag they're Ohio's best NFL team. And that ain't saying much.

Detroit became the first 0-15 team ever when it was routed 42-7 by the New Orleans Saints on Sunday. The Lions will try to avoid an perfectly awful season in the finale at Green Bay, where they haven't won since 1991.
Items.vs: Detroit Lions vs. New Orleans Saints

Items.description: Chad Pennington threw three touchdown passes and the Dolphins beat the Kansas City Chiefs 38-31 Sunday, continuing one of the most remarkable comeback seasons in NFL history in temperatures that plunged into the single digits.
Items.vs: Kansas City Chiefs vs. Miami Dolphins

Items.description: New England is peaking in time for the postseason, crushing Arizona 47-7 with a blizzard of points on a snow-covered field Sunday.
Items.vs: New England Patriots vs. Arizona Cardinals

Items.description: Isaac Bruce reached a pair of milestones in a late-game flurry in his old stadium. Both helped the San Francisco 49ers in an improbable comeback.
Items.vs: St. Louis Rams vs. San Francisco 49ers

Items.description: Philip Rivers threw for 287 yards and four touchdowns Sunday, helping the Chargers beat Tampa Bay 41-24 to keep their slim playoff hopes alive and deal a crushing blow to the Buccaneers' chances.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Buccaneers vs. San Diego Chargers

Items.description: The Tennessee Titans showed why the AFC playoffs will be running through Music City by dominating the Pittsburgh Steelers.
The Broncos blew an early 13-0 lead and lost to the Buffalo Bills 30-23, setting up an all-or-nothing game against the Chargers next week for the division title and a playoff berth.

Johnnie Lee Higgins caught a 29-yard touchdown pass and then returned a punt 80 yards for another score in the third quarter, leading the Raiders to a victory, 27-16 over the Houston Texans on Sunday.
If this is Brett Favre's kind of weather, then the magic is gone for the veteran quarterback. And so likely are the Jets' playoff chances.
Items.vs: Seattle Seahawks vs. New York Jets

Items.description: The Atlanta Falcons' stunning turnaround season will roll on into the playoffs, thanks to Matt Ryan's unflappable poise, Justin Blalock's hustle and the generosity of the Minnesota Vikings.
The Redskins stopped the Eagles on the 1-yard line on the final play to win on Sunday.
Derrick Ward ran for over 200 yards and the Giants rushed past the Panthers in OT on Sunday.
Items.vs: New York Giants vs. Carolina Panthers

Items.description: Robbie Gould kicked a 38-yard field goal with 11:28 left in overtime and the Chicago Bears overcame frigid conditions and the Green Bay Packers for a 20-17 victory Monday night to stay in the running for the playoffs.
Items.vs: Chicago Bears vs. Green Bay Packers

Items.description: Jerious Norwood ran for two touchdowns, including the go-ahead 45-yard run with 3:41 left, and the Atlanta Falcons held off the St. Louis Rams 31-27 on Sunday to clinch the No. 5 seed in the NFC.
Items.vs: Atlanta Falcons vs. St. Louis Rams

Items.description: The Patriots beat the Bills 13-0 on Sunday in windy conditions.
Items.vs: Buffalo Bills vs. New England Patriots

Items.description: Cedric Benson ran for 111 yards and a touchdown Sunday as the Bengals beat the Chiefs 16-6.
Items.vs: Cincinnati Bengals vs. Kansas City Chiefs

Items.description: The Detroit Lions own a distinction no team wants: worst in NFL history.
Items.vs: Green Bay Packers vs. Detroit Lions

Items.description: The Chicago Bears' playoff chances ended against a team long eliminated from postseason contention.
Indianapolis got those pesky milestones out of the way quickly, yanked its starters early and still managed to win its ninth straight, beating AFC South champion Tennessee 23-0 on Sunday.
Ryan Longwell's 50-yard field goal with 5 seconds left lifted the Vikings to a 20-19 victory over the resting Giants on Sunday.
Items.vs: Minnesota Vikings vs. New York Giants

Items.description: John Kasay's 42-yard field goal with a second left lifted Carolina to a 33-31 victory over the New Orleans Saints on Sunday, locking up the NFC South title and the No. 2 seed in the conference for the Panthers.
Items.vs: New Orleans Saints vs. Carolina Panthers

Items.description: Ben Roethlisberger gave the playoff-bound Steelers a major scare by sustaining a concussion during an essentially meaningless game, a 31-0 victory over the embarrassed Browns on Sunday that likely was Romeo Crennel's last as Cleveland's coach.
Oakland's Michael Bush broke two tackles, rambled through a gaping hole in the right side of the defense and headed upfield to put a dagger in Tampa Bay's slim playoff hopes.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Buccaneers vs. Oakland Raiders

Items.description: Kurt Warner and Larry Fitzgerald sent the Arizona Cardinals into the playoffs as winners.
Le'Ron McClain ran for two touchdowns in the pivotal first half, and the Ravens routed the Jacksonville Jaguars 27-7 Sunday to earn an AFC wild-card berth.
Chad Pennington walked off the field where he spent his first eight NFL seasons, surrounded by cameras and jubilant teammates after leading the Miami Dolphins to an improbable AFC East title.
Items.vs: New York Jets vs. Miami Dolphins

Items.description: Donovan McNabb flexed his muscles, seemingly mocking Terrell Owens. The always stoic Andy Reid played cheerleader, encouraging the crowd to make noise.

Joe Nedney kicked a 39-yard field goal as time expired, and the San Francisco 49ers dramatically finished their late-season surge under interim coach Mike Singletary with a 27-24 victory over the Washington Redskins on Sunday.
The mild, mild AFC West belongs to LaDainian Tomlinson, Philip Rivers and the rest of the San Diego Chargers.
Items.vs: San Diego Chargers vs. Denver Broncos

Items.description: Kurt Warner opened with a 42-yard touchdown pass to Larry Fitzgerald and connected with Anquan Boldin on a 71-yard scoring play as the Cardinals beat Atlanta 30-24.
Items.notes: NFC Wildcard Round, NFC WILD CARD PLAYOFFS

Items.description: Speedy little Darren Sproles scooted 22 yards for the winning score 6:20 into overtime and the Chargers beat the Colts 23-17 in an AFC wild-card game Saturday night.
Items.notes: AFC Wildcard Round, AFC WILD CARD PLAYOFFS
Items.vs: San Diego Chargers vs. Indianapolis Colts

Items.description: Baltimore stuffed Miami's ground attack, had no problems with the Wildcat, and harried Chad Pennington into uncharacteristic mistakes in a 27-9 victory.
Items.notes: AFC Wildcard Round, AFC WILD CARD PLAYOFFS

Items.description: All but forgotten as a postseason contender just one month earlier, Andy Reid, Donovan McNabb and the Philadelphia Eagles have a playoff win.
Items.notes: NFC Wildcard Round, NFC WILD CARD PLAYOFFS

Items.description: Matt Stover's 43-yard field goal with 53 seconds remaining Saturday lifted the Baltimore Ravens into the AFC Championship Game, 13-10 over the mistake-riddled Tennessee Titans.
Items.notes: AFC Divisional Round, AFC DIVISIONAL PLAYOFFS

Items.description: The Arizona Cardinals were expected by most to be easy prey in another futile trip to the East Coast.
Items.notes: NFC Divisional Round, NFC DIVISIONAL PLAYOFFS

Items.description: Donovan McNabb and his Philadelphia Eagles get another week to keep chasing that elusive Super Bowl crown. Eli Manning and the New York Giants get a whole offseason to wonder what went wrong.
Items.notes: NFC Divisional Round, NFC DIVISIONAL PLAYOFFS
Items.vs: New York Giants vs. Philadelphia Eagles

Items.description: Fittingly enough, the Pittsburgh Steelers brought back the home-field advantage to the NFL playoffs. Now they get to stay at home for the AFC Championship Game, and against the rival they dislike more than any other.
Items.notes: AFC Divisional Round, AFC DIVISIONAL PLAYOFFS
Items.vs: Pittsburgh Steelers vs. San Diego Chargers

Items.description: The Arizona Cardinals rallied to defeat the Philadelphia Eagles 32-25 in the NFC championship Sunday afternoon, earning the first Super Bowl trip in their long and not-so-glorious history.
Pittsburgh's dominating defense beat the Baltimore Ravens 23-14 in the AFC championship on Sunday and put the Steelers back in the Super Bowl.

Capping a remarkable fourth quarter, Santonio Holmes made a brilliant catch for a 6-yard touchdown with 35 seconds remaining to give the Pittsburgh Steelers a record sixth Super Bowl title, 27-23 over the gutty Arizona Cardinals on Sunday night.
Items.notes: Superbowl XLIII, Superbowl XLIII, SUPERBOWL XLIII

Items.description: Larry Fitzgerald caught five passes for 81 yards and two touchdowns, 44-year-old John Carney kicked two fourth-quarter field goals, and the NFC rallied to a 30-21 victory over the AFC.
